# Build context for the web image (apps/web/Dockerfile) = repo ROOT (npm workspaces).
# Keep the context to source only. Critically, EXCLUDE node_modules: the image runs `npm ci`
# to install Linux deps, and letting `COPY . .` overlay the host's (win32) node_modules would
# clobber them with wrong-platform esbuild/rollup binaries and break `vite build`. Also keep VCS,
# build output, local env/secrets, and editor/agent state out of the context and image.

# Installed dependencies (reinstalled in-image via npm ci)
**/node_modules

# VCS + agent/editor state
.git
.gitignore
.claude
.vscode
.idea

# Build output / bundles (regenerated in-image)
**/dist
**/bin
**/obj
**/TestResults

# Local-only env + secrets (never bake into an image); keep the committed *.example files
**/.env
**/.env.local
**/.env.*.local
backend/.env

# Docker + logs
**/Dockerfile
**/.dockerignore
*.log
